    c_max = max(r_prime, g_prime, b_prime)
    c_min = min(r_prime, g_prime, b_prime)
    delta = c_max - c_min

    # Hue calculation
    if delta == 0:
        h = 0
    elif c_max == r_prime:
        h = 60 * (((g_prime - b_prime) / delta) % 6)
    elif c_max == g_prime:
        h = 60 * (((b_prime - r_prime) / delta) + 2)
    else:
        h = 60 * (((r_prime - g_prime) / delta) + 4)

    # Saturation calculation
    if c_max == 0:
        s = 0
    else:
        s = (delta / c_max) * 100

    # Value calculation
    v = c_max * 100

    return (h, s, v)

This function takes in the RGB values, computes their prime form (i.e., divided by 255 to have values ranging from 0 to 1), and then calculates the hue, saturation, and value as defined in the HSV color model. The hue is calculated differently depending on which of the original values (R, G, or B) is the maximum. The saturation and value are calculated based on the maximum and the difference between the maximum and minimum of the prime values.

